questions.quote: I know! I know! And then you lose your apartment! And then you lose your job! And then your ex-wife gets married so fast! And now the coffee-ahh!! Ross, we need to talk.
Oh, this terrible! Everything is destroyed! Look at this. It obviously meant enough for me to save it, and I don't even know what it is! Ohh, it's still soft. What do you think this is?
Well, y'know what? Thanks to you I'm half way there! Ugh! Oh! I am so mad! Ross, I don't think I have ever been this angry!
Hey, do you guys think that if all those things happened, we'd still hang out?
Well... there's surrogacy, but Monica has dreamt her whole life of carrying a child, she has felt that watching a surrogate would be... too hard for her.
Five minutes ago, a line like that would've floored me. Now nothing. Well, not nothing, I am still a woman.
...And I read about these women trying to have it all, and I thank God 'Our Little Harmonica' doesn't seem to have that problem.
Where's my ring? My dead grandmother's wedding ring? Where is it? Where is it?
Look, Chandler I don't think us getting our asses kicked is a solution. Okay? Just go and find Monica!
Wait, if we're lucky, and we're really really really quiet, we may be able to hear the sound of a condom breaking!
